input: The project manager leads a team to execute the project within the project's start and end dates. Once the project is created in the project management system, a manager may initiate and later terminate the project due to its completion or for some other reason. The team executes the project. Requirements is the input of a project. As outputs the project shall produce a system. Requirements and systems are work products. Work product has a description, information of the percentage of work completed, and may be validated. The validation is depending on the type of work product. The requirements are validated with users in workshops. System are validated by being tested against the requirements. The requirements may be published using various types of media, including on an intranet or paper form. Systems may be deployed onto specific plataforms.

Model a movie shooting domain: a Scene has many Setups; each Setup has many Takes (tk_of_stp). Scenes may be Internal or External; External scenes are located at a Location. Capture codes, descriptions, and take measurements.
actual_output:
@startuml

abstract class Scene {
    - code: String
    - description: String
    --
    + Scene(code: String, description: String)
    + getCode(): String
    + getDescription(): String
    + setCode(code: String): void
    + setDescription(description: String): void
}

class Setup {
    - code: String
    - description: String
    - scene: Scene
    --
    + Setup(code: String, description: String, scene: Scene)
    + getCode(): String
    + getDescription(): String
    + setCode(code: String): void
    + setDescription(description: String): void
    + getScene(): Scene
}

class Take {
    - number: int
    - filmLength: double
    - reelCode: String
    - setup: Setup
    --
    + Take(number: int, filmLength: double, reelCode: String, setup: Setup)
    + getNumber(): int
    + getFilmLength(): double
    + getReelCode(): String
    + setNumber(number: int): void
    + setFilmLength(length: double): void
    + setReelCode(code: String): void
    + isValidNumber(): boolean
    + getSetup(): Setup
}

class Location {
    - code: String
    - address: String
    - description: String
    --
    + Location(code: String, address: String, description: String)
    + getCode(): String
    + getAddress(): String
    + getDescription(): String
    + setCode(code: String): void
    + setAddress(address: String): void
    + setDescription(description: String): void
}

class InternalScene {
    --
    + InternalScene(code: String, description: String)
    + isTheaterScene(): boolean
}

class ExternalScene {
    - sceneType: String
    - location: Location
    --
    + ExternalScene(code: String, description: String, sceneType: String, location: Location)
    + getSceneType(): String
    + setSceneType(type: String): void
    + isDayScene(): boolean
    + isNightScene(): boolean
    + isValidSceneType(): boolean
    + getLocation(): Location
    + setLocation(location: Location): void
}

Scene "1" *-- "1..*" Setup : contains >
Setup "1" *-- "1..*" Take : contains >
Scene <|-- InternalScene
Scene <|-- ExternalScene
ExternalScene "1..*" -- "1" Location : filmed at >

note bottom of Take
  number must be positive
end note

note right of ExternalScene
  sceneType can be "day" or "night"
end note

@enduml

Model a document editor. A Document has many Pages. A Page can show Trimming (date, time, pageNumber) and may contain Characters, Tables, and Pictures. Characters, Tables and Pictures can appear in Cells; tables aggregate cells. Capture basic operations like insert/hide/edit.
expected_output:
@startuml
class Document{
    - numberOfPages
    + open()
    + save()
    + print()
    + new()
}
class Page{
    - pageNumber
    + newPage()
    + hideHeader()
    + hideFooter()
    + insertPicture()
    + insertTable()
}
class Trimming{
    - date
    - time
    - pageNumber
    + display()
    + change()
    + hide()
}
class Character{
    - ASCIICode
    - type
    + normal()
    + italic()
    + bold()
    + underline()
}
class Table{
    - rows
    - columns
    + insertRow()
    + insertColumn()
    + newTable()
    + insertPicture()
}
class Picture{
    - imageType
    - imageSize
    + insert()
    + delete()
}
class Cell{
    - cellFormat
    + edit()
}
Document "1" *-- "1..*" Page
Page "1" o--  "0..1" Trimming
Page "1" o--  "0..*" Character
Page "1" o--  "0..*" Table
Page "1" o--  "0..*" Picture
Character "0..*" --o "1" Cell
Table "1" *-- "1..*" Cell  
Picture "0..*" --o "1" Cell


@enduml
